But now I have to stop avoiding and maybe get to work on those ever-waiting papers. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8o --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/nerd.gif ALT="8o"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#b9a1d0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bchristlikebooklovers.showUserPublicProfile?gid=femalenomad>FemaleNomad</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>ezHopeful</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#3333ff>(12/7/02 12:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fchristlikebookloversfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=24.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> 7th</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :party --><img src=http://www.myezboard.com/projects/ezboard/ezboard_userimages/godlovers80868/images/ACF2837.gif ALT=":party"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Two papers done!<br>
<br>
...Only 3 to go. But I think I can write half of one today at work, and another one maybe tonight? Well...we'll see. Then that leaves just the BIG SCARY ONE for next week! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#9fb7df><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bchristlikebooklovers.showUserPublicProfile?gid=femalenomad>FemaleNomad</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>ezHopeful</span><br>  Posts: 14<br> <font color=#3333ff>(2/13/03 4:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fchristlikebookloversfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=24.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> 13 Feb</span><hr size=1> I think I am going to have to come back here more often. Because ever since I came back from my trip (Aussie was fab. Not spectacular, but still fab), I have been having ISSUES!<br>
<br>
I think I need therapy, but why? I mean, I am functional, probably even more than fuctional. Just because I feel all lost and out of control-like? Please. There are other people who have real problems.<br>
<br>
Add to that, I have spent my entire life being the one with the answers, the one other people go to for help. I don't share my problems with the world (at least, not until I can't handle them anymore). Not my real problems, anyway. Sure, I complain, but who doesn't?<br>
<br>
I'm whining.<br>
<br>
Anyway, let's talk about what I'm reading at the moment. Just a few books (I can't decide which to finish first, so I'm reading them all):<br>
<br>
Almost French, by Sarah Turnbull. It's another travel book, about an Australian journalist who left her old life and now resides in Paris, with all the challenges and culture shock that involves.<br>
<br>
The Crimson Petal and the White. Definitely not a book I'd recommend to most of the people who visit CLBL, GLO, and all the rest, but spectacularly well-written and involving. It follows the life of a 19th century London prostitute. <br>
<br>
The Two Towers. I have almost a year to finish it before the Return of the King comes to the theatres.<br>
<br>
Making a Literary Life, by Carolyn See. A beautiful, fabulous book about writing and being a writer - I highly recommend it to anyone - ANYONE - who really wants to write.<br>
<br>
And textbooks. I am going to pick up a copy of the Koran this afternoon, I think, too. And I'm reading the psalms. Wow!<br>
